{How Purdy Won #14} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 {Alekine's suggestion (but never played) as a result of Tartakower's use of 3.Be2 in the New York 1924 tournament in which he scored 2.5/1.5.} 4. e4 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. h3 a5 7. Bg5 Na6 8. Be2 (8. Nd2) 8... Qe8 9. e5 (9. g4 c6 (9... e5 10. d5) 10. Qd2 d5 11. exd5 cxd5 12. Bxf6 exf6 13. Nxd5) 9... dxe5 (9... Nd7 10. exd6 exd6 (10... cxd6 11. O-O Nf6 {The book doesn't give the continuation:} 12. Re1) 11. O-O Nf6 (11... Nb6 12. Re1 Qd7 $3 (12... f6 13. Bf4 Qf7 14. b3) 13. Bd3 Re8 14. Qd2) 12. Re1 c6 (12... Bd7 $1 13. Qd2) (12... Qd8 13. Bf1) 13. Qd2) 10. dxe5 Nd7 11. Nd5 f6 12. exf6 exf6 13. Be3 (13. Bf4 c6 14. Nc3) 13... c6 14. Nc3 Qe7 15. O-O Ndc5 0-1


