{Purdy: 'How Purdy Won #8''How Purdy Won #8 Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Purdy: 'How Purdy Won #8'''} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bb5 Bb4 5. O-O O-O 6. d3 d6 7. Bg5 Bxc3 8. bxc3 Qe7 $1 {Purdy: 'This followed by d8-e6 is the Metger Defence.''This followed by d8-e6 is the Metger Defence. Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Purdy: 'This followed by d8-e6 is the Metger Defence.'''} 9. Re1 (9. Bxc6 bxc6 10. Nd2 Qe6 11. Bxf6 Qxf6 12. Qf3 {Purdy: '=' '=''Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Purdy: '='''}) 9... Nd8 10. d4 Ne6 11. Bc1 $1 c5 {Purdy: '!' '!''Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Purdy: '!'''} 12. g3 {Nach Purdy: 'Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Nach''} (12. dxe5 dxe5 13. Nxe5 $2 {Purdy: '??' '??''Deutsche Schachzeitung: '?' Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Purdy: '??''' verliert Weiss eine Figur. Purdy: 'Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'verliert Weiss eine Figur.''} Nc7 $19) 12... Qc7 {Purdy: '!' '!''Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Purdy: '!''' Purdy: '...c4''...c4 Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Purdy: '...c4'''} 13. d5 $1 ({If} 13. Bf1 c4 {and Black has carried out his plan.}) 13... c4 $1 14. dxe6 Bxe6 {Purdy: 'White cannot retain his piece. Out of many possible variations he now selects the only one that avoids disadvantage.''White cannot retain his piece. Out of many possible variations he now selects the only one that avoids disadvantage. Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Purdy: 'White cannot retain his piece. Out of many possible variations he now selects the only one that avoids disadvantage.''' Weiss kann die gewonnene Figur nicht halten. Unter vielen Möglichkeiten wählt er nun die, welche Nachteil vermeidet. Purdy: 'Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Weiss kann die gewonnene Figur nicht halten. Unter vielen Möglichkeiten wählt er nun die, welche Nachteil vermeidet.''} 15. Bg5 $1 {Purdy: 'Deutsche Schachzeitung: '!''} a6 16. Bxf6 $1 {Purdy: 'Deutsche Schachzeitung: '!''} gxf6 17. Ba4 b5 18. Nh4 $1 {Purdy: 'By weakening Black's k-side and not attempting to regain his lost pawn, White assures himself of a counter-attack to balance his bad q-side.''By weakening Black's k-side and not attempting to regain his lost pawn, White assures himself of a counter-attack to balance his bad q-side. Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Purdy: 'By weakening Black's k-side and not attempting to regain his lost pawn, White assures himself of a counter-attack to balance his bad q-side.'''} bxa4 19. Qh5 $1 {Purdy: 'Deutsche Schachzeitung: '!''} Rfb8 20. g4 Rb2 21. Qh6 {Purdy: '!' '!' Purdy: 'Black threatened to get his king away, give up the h-pawn, and then prosecute his q-side attack in safety.''Black threatened to get his king away, give up the h-pawn, and then prosecute his q-side attack in safety. Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Purdy: '!' Purdy: 'Black threatened to get his king away, give up the h-pawn, and then prosecute his q-side attack in safety.'''} Qe7 22. Nf5 (22. Re3 Kh8 {und Schwarz steht ganz sicher.}) 22... Bxf5 23. gxf5 {Purdy: 'After''After Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Purdy: 'After'''} Qf8 {Purdy: '!' '!''Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Purdy: '!''' Purdy: 'White actually intended''White actually intended Deutsche Schachzeitung: 'Purdy: 'White actually intended'''} 24. Qc1 $5 (24. Qh4 {Purdy} Qg7+ 25. Kh1 Kf8 26. Rg1 Qh8 27. Qh6+ Ke7 28. Rg7 Rab8 29. Rag1 $1 Rb1 30. Rxh7 Rxg1+ 31. Kxg1 Rb1+ 32. Kg2 Qf8 33. Qxf8+ Kxf8 $11) 24... a3 25. Kh1 h6 26. Rg1+ Kh7 27. Rg4 {when Black might have winning chances with} Rab8 28. h3 R8b5 29. Rh4 (29. Qd1 d5 $1) 29... d5 30. exd5 Rxd5 31. Rxc4 $5 Rc5 $1 32. Qf1 Qc8 $1 1/2-1/2


