{Purdy's last CC game, the only one completed by him after the World Ch Final since he never entered another CC tournament. See "How Purdy Won" pp168-70 and Game 44. The Swedish newspaper AftonTidningen ran a "dearest wish" feature and each week one such wish was drawn and they tried to fulfil it. Early in 1956 Elis Hugolf, a well-known Swedish CC player, had his dearest wish drawn, and it was to play a game with the World Champion. Purdy agreed.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. Qe2 (5. O-O Nxe4) 5... Be7 6. O-O b5 7. Bb3 d6 (7... O-O 8. c3 d5 9. d3) 8. c3 O-O 9. d4 Bg4 10. d5 Na5 11. Bc2 c6 12. dxc6 Qb6 13. Rd1 Rfc8 14. Na3 $2 (14. h3 $142 Be6 (14... Bh5 15. g4 Bg6 16. Nh4 $16)) 14... Qxc6 15. Bd3 Nb7 $1 16. c4 (16. Re1 {Purdy}) 16... bxc4 17. Bxc4 (17. Nxc4 Nc5 18. Ncd2 Nxd3 19. Qxd3 Qc2 $17) 17... Nc5 18. Bd5 Nxd5 19. exd5 Qb7 20. h3 $8 Bh5 21. g4 Bg6 22. Nc4 Be4 23. Ng5 Bxd5 24. Na5 Qb6 25. Rxd5 Qxa5 26. Ne4 Qb4 27. Nxd6 $2 (27. Nxc5 Rxc5 $19) 27... Bxd6 28. Rxd6 Nb3 0-1


