{How Purdy Won #10} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Bg2 dxc4 5. Qa4+ Nbd7 6. Nc3 c5 7. Bf4 $5 Be7 8. Nb5 O-O 9. Nc7 (9. Bc7 Qe8 10. Nd6 Nb6 $1) 9... Rb8 10. Qxa7 $2 ({The right move was} 10. Nb5 $1 {playing for a draw by repetition. To avoid the draw, Black was considering} a6 11. Bc7 $3 (11. Bxb8 Nxb8 $1 12. Nc3 cxd4 $17) 11... axb5 $1 12. Bxd8 bxa4 13. Bxe7 cxd4 $1 14. Bxf8 Kxf8 {when Black comes out with two pawns for the exchange, with equal chances.}) 10... cxd4 11. Nf3 (11. Nxe6 fxe6 12. Bxb8 Bc5 13. Qa8 Qb6 14. O-O-O Nxb8 15. Qxb8 Ba3 $3 $19) 11... Bb4+ $19 12. Kf1 Bc5 13. Qa4 Qe7 14. Nb5 e5 15. Bc1 Nb6 16. Qc2 Bd7 17. Na3 e4 18. Ng5 d3 19. Qd1 h6 20. Nh3 c3 {Truly a lesson in the danger of premature attacks!} 0-1


