{How Purdy Won #42} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 O-O 8. c3 d6 9. d4 Bg4 10. Be3 exd4 11. cxd4 Na5 12. Bc2 Nc4 13. Bc1 c5 14. b3 Na5 15. Nbd2 (15. d5 $1) 15... Nc6 16. h3 Bh5 17. g4 Bg6 18. Bb2 Nd7 19. Rc1 Re8 20. Nf1 Bf6 21. Bb1 Qb6 22. dxc5 dxc5 23. Bxf6 Nxf6 24. e5 Red8 25. Qe2 Bxb1 26. exf6 Bd3 27. Qe3 Nb4 28. Qxc5 Qxc5 (28... Qxf6 $142) 29. Rxc5 Nxa2 30. Re7 $1 Nb4 31. Ne3 Rac8 32. Rxc8 Rxc8 33. Nd4 $1 gxf6 34. Ndf5 Nc6 35. Rd7 Bxf5 36. Nxf5 a5 37. Nh6+ Kf8 38. Rxf7+ Ke8 39. Rxh7 Nd4 (39... a4 40. bxa4 bxa4 41. Ng8 $1) 40. Ra7 Nxb3 (40... Rc3 $5 41. Ng8 $1) 41. Nf5 Rb8 $2 {Purdy had set up the position with his pawn on b4. He later claimed that he had a drawing line by} (41... Kd8 {and played a friendly afterwards to test this, but more recent analysis shows White probably has a won position.} 42. Nd6 Rb8 43. h4 Nc5 44. h5 $1 {Mitchell played 44 xa5 in the friendly and a draw resulted.} Nd7 45. Nb7+ $18) 42. h4 Nc5 43. h5 Nd7 44. h6 Nf8 45. Ng7+ 1-0


