{How Purdy Won #41} 1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nxd4 Bb4 6. g3 {Purdy thought this was a new move but Malmgren found pre-war precedents.} (6. Bg5) 6... Ne5 $1 (6... Bxc3+) (6... Ne4) 7. Qb3 Qe7 {7.-Lc3:+ 8. Dc3: d5(Euwe), doch 9. Lg2! Sc4: 10. e4 Sb6 11. e5 Sb5(Purdy)} 8. Be3 (8. Bg2 Qc5 9. Nc2 Nfg4 $17 {Bernards-Folkmann, IFSB corr 1933}) 8... Ne4 9. Ndb5 $1 (9. Bg2 $6 {Bernards-Muller, IFSB}) 9... Bxc3+ 10. Nxc3 Nxc3 11. Qxc3 O-O 12. Bg2 d6 13. O-O Re8 14. Rad1 {15. Ld4 f6 16. e4 f4} (14. c5 $1 c6 15. cxd6 Qxd6 16. Rad1 Qc7 17. Bc5 f6 18. Rd2 $16 {Berkavicius-Dr.van Kol (corr). Presumably Malmgren had prepared some improvement on this.}) 14... Nc6 $1 15. Rd2 Bf5 16. c5 dxc5 17. Bxc5 Qe5 {Zum Ausgleich das einzige(Euwe)} 18. Qxe5 (18. Qc1 $1 {Malmgren}) 18... Rxe5 19. Be3 {20. Lf4} Be4 20. Bh3 $5 {(20. f3)} Rd5 21. Rxd5 (21. Rc1 $5) 21... Bxd5 22. Rd1 $1 Bxa2 23. Rd7 Bc4 24. Rxc7 Bxe2 25. Rxb7 Bf3 26. Bg2 (26. Rc7 {Tc8,}) 26... Bxg2 27. Kxg2 a5 $1 28. Kf3 f6 29. Ke4 a4 30. Bc5 Ne5 31. h4 (31. f4 Nc4 $1 32. Kd3 a3 $3) (31. Ra7 Rb8 32. Ba3 Nc4 $11) 31... Re8 $1 (31... Nc4 32. Ba3 $18) 32. Kd5 Rd8+ 33. Ke4 Re8 34. Ba3 h5 (34... Nc4+ $14) 35. Re7 Rb8 {36.- Sc4 =} 36. Rc7 Rb3 37. Rc8+ Kf7 (37... Kh7 $5) 38. Rc7+ Kg8 39. Rc8+ Kf7 40. f4 Ng4 41. f5 $1 Nf2+ 42. Kd5 g6 43. Rc7+ Kg8 44. Ra7 (44. fxg6 Rxg3 $1 45. g7 f5 (45... Rxg7 {Purdy}) 46. Bf8 (46. Bc5 {Purdy}) 46... f4 $1 $19) 44... gxf5 45. Ke6 $1 (45. Rxa4 $2 Kg7 $19) 45... Rxg3 $1 (45... Nd1 $2 46. Kxf5 Nxb2 47. Bd6 $1 $18 Rb6 48. Kg6) 46. Rxa4 {46.- Tg4 47.Ta8+ Kg7 48.Kf5: Th4: 49.Ta7+ Kg8 50. Kf6: Tg4 51.Ta8+ Kh7 52.Ta7=} 1/2-1/2


