{How Purdy Won #40} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3 O-O 9. h3 Na5 10. Bc2 c5 11. d4 Qc7 12. Bg5 $5 h6 $1 13. Bh4 Nc6 14. Nbd2 Nh5 $1 15. Bxe7 Nxe7 16. Nf1 Nf4 17. Ne3 Bb7 18. g3 $1 cxd4 (18... Nxh3+ 19. Kg2 Ng5 20. Nxg5 hxg5 21. Qh5 $40) 19. cxd4 Nfg6 20. Rc1 Rac8 21. h4 Rfe8 22. h5 Nf8 23. d5 Qd7 24. Nh4 Nh7 25. a4 Rc7 26. axb5 $6 (26. Ra1) 26... Qxb5 27. b3 Bc8 28. Ra1 Rc3 29. g4 (29. Nc4 $2 Qc5 {30.- Tg3:+} 30. Kg2 Bh3+ $3 $19) 29... Bd7 30. Kg2 Rec8 31. Nc4 $1 Qb4 $1 (31... Bxg4 32. Qxg4 Rxc2 33. Re3 $16) 32. Re3 (32. Rxa6 $4 Rxc2 $19) (32. Re3 Rxe3 33. Nxe3 a5 $1 $17 {This move was discovered by Purdy years aftre the game ended.} (33... Bb5 34. Nf3 $1 Nf6 35. Nd2 Nd7 36. Ndc4 Rb8 37. Qe1 $11 {Purdy in Mail Chess})) 1/2-1/2


