{How Purdy Won #3; first game to finish in the match.} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nc3 Bf5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Nge2 $5 (6. Bc4) 6... Qa5 $5 7. f3 $2 e5 $1 8. e4 exd4 $1 9. Qxd4 Nb4 $1 10. Qd1 N8a6 $1 { The best chance now was 11 g3. The move played threatens to trap a  by a3, but McIntosh shows he can permanently leave his  en prise.} 11. Nf4 Rd8 12. Bd2 Bd6 13. Qb1 Nc5 14. Nfd5 $2 {Purdy: "An oversight but the thin ice on which White ahs been skating has already cracked".} cxd5 15. Nxd5 Bg3+ $1 16. hxg3 Rxd5 17. Qd1 Qb6 $1 {A fine move, curtailing resistance.} 18. Bb5+ Bd7 $1 {If 19 exf5 cd3+ 20 xd3 xd3 21 e2 b5! 22 g1 c2+ 23 e1 0-0! mating or winning the .} 0-1


