{How Purdy Won #27. Purdy's opponent represented the Belgium II team. This is a very complicated game, analyse din enormous detail in the book.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 b6 4. Bd3 Bb7 5. Nbd2 c5 6. O-O Nc6 7. c3 Qc7 8. dxc5 bxc5 9. e4 Be7 10. Re1 O-O 11. e5 Ng4 12. Nc4 f6 13. Qc2 $1 {The only move to give Black serious problems.} fxe5 $6 (13... Ncxe5 $5 $13 {Purdy}) (13... h6 $1 {Frank Hutchings}) 14. Bxh7+ (14. h3 e4 15. Bxe4 Nf6 16. Bd3 d5 17. Nce5 c4 18. Bf1 Ne4 {Purdy} 19. Nxc4 {Hutchings}) 14... Kh8 15. Re4 $6 (15. h3 $1) 15... Nxf2 $1 16. Qxf2 $2 Kxh7 17. Rh4+ Kg8 $1 18. Rh3 e4 19. Qc2 d5 20. Ng5 Bxg5 21. Bxg5 Rf5 22. Rg3 dxc4 23. Qxe4 Nd4 24. Qe3 Re5 25. Bf4 Rxe3 26. Bxc7 Ne2+ 27. Kf2 Nxg3 28. Kxe3 Nf5+ 29. Kf2 Rf8 30. Kg1 Nh4 {Adjudicated won for Black.} 0-1


