1. e4 {Purdy Purdy Purdy Purdy Purdy Purdy: 'Purdy/Salm' Purdy: 'Purdy/Salm Myers Salm Purdy' Purdy: 'Myers Salm Purdy'} c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Be2 Bg7 7. Be3 Nc6 8. Qd2 O-O 9. f4 $1 {Purdy: 'Purdy/Salm: '!'' Playing this before castling was an idea of my own. Purdy: 'Purdy/Salm: 'Playing this before castling was an idea of my own.''} Bd7 {If now Purdy: 'Purdy/Salm: 'If now''} (9... Ng4 {Purdy: 'Purdy/Salm'} 10. Bxg4 Bxg4 {White can already play} 11. f5 $1 {threatening to catch the bishop. Best for Black then, I think is} Nxd4 $1 12. Bxd4 e5 $1 13. Bf2 gxf5 14. h3 Bh5 15. exf5 f6 {White seems to get at any rate a prefereble game with} 16. Nd5 {prevents...a5} Qd7 {say} 17. O-O {to be considered is g4 followed by 0-0-0. white has a healthy initiative. Neither of Black's bishops is very good, and one is very bad.}) (9... e5 {Purdy: 'Purdy/Salm'} 10. Nxc6 bxc6 11. O-O-O Ng4 (11... Qa5 12. Qxd6 Ng4 13. Qc5 $1) 12. Bc5 $1) 10. O-O a6 (10... Ng4 {Purdy} 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. Bd4 Bxd4+ 13. Qxd4 Qb6 14. Qxb6 axb6 15. Bxg4 Bxg4 16. f5 gxf5 17. h3 Bh5 18. exf5 f6 19. Rae1 Rfe8 20. Rf4 Bf7 21. Rb4 Ra6 22. a3 h5 23. Ne2 Kf8 24. Re4 d5 25. Re3 e5 26. fxe6 Rxe6 27. Rxe6 Bxe6 28. Nf4 Bf7 29. Ne6+ Kg8 30. Nd8 c5 31. Re7 Bg6 32. c3 Ra5 33. Nc6 Ra6 34. Re6 Kf7 35. Nd8+ Kg7 36. Rd6 Be4 37. Ne6+ Kf7 38. Nxc5 Ke7 39. Re6+ Kf7 40. Rc6 Ra5 41. Nb7 Ra7 42. Rxb6 {1-0 Pillsbury,H-Howell,C/Buffalo USA 1901/}) (10... Nxd4 {Purdy} 11. Bxd4 Bc6 12. Bf3 Qc7 (12... e5 13. Be3 exf4 14. Bxf4 Qb6+ 15. Kh1 Qxb2 16. Rab1 Qa3 17. Rb3 Qa6 18. Be2 Qa5 19. Bxd6 Rfd8 20. Qf4 Rd7 21. Bb4 Qd8 22. Ba3 Qe8 23. Bd3 Rad8 24. Qh4 Qe6 25. Bc1 Re8 26. Bg5 Nxe4 27. Nxe4 Bxe4 28. Bxe4 Rd4 29. Rxb7 Rxe4 30. Qf2 f5 31. Qxa7 Bd4 32. Qa5 Rg4 33. Qc7 Rxg5 34. Qxh7+ Kf8 35. Qh6+ Kg8 36. Qxg5 Qa6 37. Rfb1 Bg7 38. Qd2 Re2 39. Qd8+ Bf8 40. Rb8 Qa3 41. Qf6 Qe7 42. Rxf8+ Qxf8 43. Qxg6+ {1-0 Kopa,I-Leussen,B/Barmen GER 1905/}) 13. Nd5 Bxd5 14. exd5 Rfe8 15. Rad1 Rac8 16. Rf2 b6 17. c3 Qd7 18. h3 h5 19. Qd3 B